article.headline: Cal State Fullerton 76, Pacific 70
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. (AP) -- Bobby Brown scored 21 points to lead Cal State Fullerton to a 76-70 victory over Pacific on Saturday night. Scott Cutley added 16 points and nine rebounds for the Titans (12-3, 3-1 Big West), who have won seven of eight and earned their first victory over Pacific since 2003. Anthony Brown had 16 points and 10 rebounds for the Tigers (5-10, 2-1 Big West), who have lost seven of their last nine. Reggie Vezia added 14 points. Fullerton, which led by as many as 16 points in the first half, held a 36-23 lead before Pacific used a 14-2 surge to narrow the deficit to 38-37 with 16:12 to play. Vezia and Anthony Esparza each scored five points during the run. But Cutley scored eight points and grabbed three rebounds during a 13-1 spree that give the Titans a 68-54 advantage with 2:16 remaining. Fullerton won its 12th consecutive home game over two seasons and its first at home over Pacific since 1999.
